msgstr ""
"Project-Id-Version: Orbiter Flights\n"
"Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8\n"
"Plural-Forms: nplurals=2; plural=(n != 1);\n"
"Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit\n"

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:4
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "DG-ISS Sync-Dock, rendezvous-docking recording for \"Go Play In Space\" 2nd Edition, chapter 5 \"Dancing in the Dark.\"  Note that the docking HUD is displayed, that the Sync Orbit MFD is on the left..."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:6
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "...and the Orbit MFD is on the right.  First thing to do is time accelerate to get the ISS to our ship's periapsis so we can note the altitude there...              time accelerating........"
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:9
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Note that our orbital planes are already aligned (Inc), but our position (green line) is ahead of the ISS position (ISS), so we need to get into a slightly bigger, longer period orbit so the ISS can catch up with us."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:13
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "1000x warp factor, the Earth is really zipping by..."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:15
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Slowing time to 100x"
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:18
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The docking HUD shows a box around the target (ISS) when in field of view, or an arrow pointing to it if off-screen.  A circle with a plus sign shows ISS relative velocity, with V[ISS] pointing to it when off-screen."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:21
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Note that when the ISS target box goes off-screen, the ISS arrow appears."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:23
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Back to 1x (real time)."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:26
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Note that as the ISS (yellow line) reaches our periapsis (green dot), its (yellow) Alt value in Orbit MFD is 360.3 km.  "
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:29
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The next thing to do is accelerate to apoapsis where a small prograde burn can raise our PeA to match the ISS...     time accelerating... "
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:33
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "...now back to 1x."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:36
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Turning prograde for the burn, noting the DTMin on Sync MFD is about 44 s and raising the PeA to 360.3k will decrease this, but not to zero."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:38
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Firing short bursts of main engine (numpad + key) to raise PeA to 360.3k to match ISS height at this point."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:40
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Still in Prograde mode, switching to translation [LIN] mode to tweak PeA with forward (num-6) and backward (num-9) thrusts."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:42
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "OK, our PeA is now 360.3k, matching ISS altitude at our periapsis.  Get ready to warp time 10-100x again..."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:46
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Time warping at 100x to quickly coast to periapsis where we can fire prograde and raise our apoapsis to increase our orbital period (T) slightly, allowing the ISS to catch up with us."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:48
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Sunrise over eastern Europe.  The Sync Orbit MFD shows a yellow line on the orbit where closest approach occurs.  The two columns are times to the reference point for ship and target."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:51
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Other key Sync MFD numbers are Dist (to target) and RVel (relative velocity). Note also that RInc is shown as 0.00 degrees (planes aligned).  Coming up on periapsis..."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:54
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Back at 1x time, thrusters still LIN, linear thruster num-6/9 bursts (fwd-back) will adjust DTMin to nearly zero."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:56
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Kill Rotation to turn off Prograde, and now we time accelerate for a couple of orbits to reach the orbit where DTMin=0 and the ISS will hopefully be close by (but not too close, a few km)."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:59
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Note that DG period (T) is now 5.540k s, vs. 5.501k for ISS, 39 s longer for us, so ISS can catch up.  "
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:61
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "We've got a couple of orbits to fast forward through, so we'll just show a few progress reports."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:63
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Yellow line is orbit 1 (Ob 1), so really two orbits to go (we intercept on orbit zero)."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:64
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Another sunset, ISS target box passes 403 km away."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:66
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Just passed our reference point, now on orbit zero, 5.314k seconds Sh-ToR, Dist 304.3k, an orbit away from intercept."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:69
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "ISS should be just visible in target box, 46 km away."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:73
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Note that the yellow numbers are now on orbit zero (Ob 0) and the Sh-ToR time value is getting smaller as we approach the rendezvous point."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:75
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The ISS has been barely visible in darkness framed by the target box in the HUD, but now sunrise is approaching, and the ISS will momentarily be backlit against the Earth's limb (distance about 10 km). "
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:78
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Coming out of warp shortly since the ISS is getting close - at around 3.5 km, we will enter ROT mode and rotate the ship to point at the V[ISS] ball. "
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:81
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Rotating (yaw right) to point at V[ISS] which is now behind us.  We want to put the direction symbol on the velocity indicator, preparing to zero out our relative velocity to ISS."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:83
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Nearly pointing at V[ISS] symbol, so kill rotation (num-5).  ISS range still closing at 18.69 m/s, waiting until Dist is under 2 km to zero out V[ISS]."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:84
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Any time now, I should start braking..."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:86
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Any time now, right here over Stuttgart..."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:88
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "WHAT AM I WAITING FOR!?!!?!"
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:89
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "FINALLY!"
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:91
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "This is a very long burst of forward LIN thruster that is not slowing us down all that much.  A bit disappointing, and the ISS is getting quite close."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:94
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Yikes! Blimey! Oy! Waited too long to start braking.  The LIN thrusters are clearly not enough, so we will need a few bursts of main engines to avoid colliding with ISS!"
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:96
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "We've slowed down but still chasing the V[ISS] symbol and using thrusters to take out residual velocity. "
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:99
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "That was a bit close!  Range only ~800 m but relative V is near zero, so time to pitch down to put the nose on the ISS and see how it looks for docking."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:101
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The ISS is on the nose, 800 m away and (thankfully) not closing (yet)! Click [PWR] button on now unneeded Sync MFD on left side to improve visibility.  Or if you want to stop that beeping, click [SEL], then [Radio/MP3 Panel], then [RAD], then [PWR]. "
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:104
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "On right MFD, QUICKLY click [SEL] then [Docking] then click [NAV] three times to reach NAV4 for docking port D-01.  Then click the [HUD] button.  I'm rotating right away to aim for those boxes..."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:106
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "[LIN] mode, thrusting forward to start closing on the outer docking boxes, NOT on the ISS itself (yet)."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:107
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Compare the Dock MFD to the outside view - ISS to left and down, + (target) symbol on MFD to left and down."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:109
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The range is closing slowly but I don't want to get fast near the ISS, so I use a little 10x time warpage."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:112 Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:120
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Back to 1x time."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:115
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Still impatient, still closing slowly, use a little more 10x time warpology."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:118
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "As we pass the ISS off to the left, CVEL goes negative and distance increases. We head for the outer boxes to allow time to get lined up with the port."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:121
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The goal here?  To try to center ourselves inside one of the outer HUD docking boxes, and both aligned with and level with the docking port.  "
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:123
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Rotate left to get ISS and boxes back in view.  Also want to put the \"cross\" (-V[ISS] symbol) back in the boxes since this is our direction relative to ISS."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:124
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Now closing on boxes, rotating for rough line-up with them, want double line at top for correct orientation to docking port."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:125
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Dock MFD shows no visible X (angular alignment indicator), so angle alignment is poor, rotate to line up better. ISS is \"below\" on the MFD."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:126
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Pitching up, red X comes into view on MFD; we need to center it (with ROT thrusters only) in MFD for correct angular alignment with port's axis."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:127
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Rotations get the X roughly centered and changed to white, temporarily stable, then start to adjust linear position."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:128
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "LIN mode, thrusting TOWARD the MFD cross (left, right, up, down) to try to get it lined up."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:129
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "CVEL close to zero to allow time for alignment.  We are centered better in the docking boxes, but MFD cross is still off center."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:130
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "ROT mode, roll to put the solid white arrow at top of MFD target for rotational alignment."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:131
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Left-right lineup of cross looks good, ISS target still a bit high and rotation X still a bit off center."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:132
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Tweak the rotation cross centering just a small amount (Cntrl-Thrusters)."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:133
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Distance under 160 m, CVEL 0.21, still chasing lineup with linear thrusters."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:134
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Working LIN thrusters to control transverse drift and to put HUD plus-symbol (-V[ISS]) just above docking port."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:135
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Lineup looks good, DST 135 m, CVEL 0.26"
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:136
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Lineup good, 105 m, CVEL 0.29"
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:137
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Fixing up a little drift, range 90 m, closing at 0.29 m/s"
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:138
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Good lineup, 60 m, HUD -V cross just above dock port (acounts for offset between DG eye and docking port)."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:139
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Lineup OK, 50 m, CVEL 0.29"
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:140
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Good lineup, 20 m, CVEL .28"
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:141
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Slight drift, 10 m, .28 CVEL"
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:142
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "At 2.5 m, reverse thruster (num-9) to reduce CVEL, CVEL 0.14, dropping..."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG-ISS Sync Dock/system.dat:143
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Range 1 m, CVEL 0.11, about to dock."
msgstr ""

